    "client_msg_id": "77c7a299-6301-42c9-8300-5faacff1feab",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Think of it this way.  Tangled node-edge graphs aren't the best.  If your graph is planer, then you can lay it out on a grid (more or less).  With the geometry of the grid corresponding to the connectedness of the graph, you don't need edges anymore.\n\nThree dimensions of course is enough to keep wires from intersecting.  And with more dimensions, you can keep wires from snaking...",
